{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place trout into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place water and gelatine into mixing bowl and stand for 2 minutes, then cook <nobr>1 min\/90°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add stock paste and blend <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Add spring onions\/shallots, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, pepper, cream cheese, Tabasco® (optional) and half of the reserved trout and blend <nobr>20 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add cream and blend <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add remaining trout and stir <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Divide pâté between 4 small ramekins (125ml), cover with plastic wrap, then place into refrigerator for a minimum of 3 hours to set (see Tips). Serve once chilled."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 g hot smoked trout (see Tips)","120 g water","1 tsp gelatine powder","1 tsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","2 - 3 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into pieces","60 g mayonnaise (see Tips)","2 tsp lemon juice","salt, to taste","ground black pepper, to taste","120 g cream cheese","2 - 3 drops Tabasco® sauce (optional)","120 g pouring (whipping) cream"]}],"id":"r256146","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-DfB2dRTfrFo\/XZMvg8-r69I\/AAAAAAAAaS0\/MKEFxHTKDgY9RsPVdVgvObjYfEGgUgZ2gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_hvu0fGhxyIYk78Cr.png","title":"Smoked trout pâté","publishedAt":"2018-03-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17.6 g","fat":"38.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"1.8 g","calories":"1756.6 kJ \/ 418.2 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, ramekins (125 ml), plastic wrap, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["You can buy hot smoked trout at most major supermarkets or from some fish mongers.","Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","To make your own mayonnaise, refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> or <i>Everyday Cookbook<\/i>.","We serve this dish right in the ramekin, but to turn it out, simply line your ramekins with plastic wrap - allowing approx. 5 cm of overhang - before filling with pâté. Once chilled, use the plastic wrap to easily remove it from the ramekins.","<strong>Crayfish pâté<\/strong>: Replace the hot smoked trout with 200 g cooked crayfish, then proceed as per recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","3h 15m","4 portions"]}